        -- Posted by Kojaru on 12:04 am on Oct. 20, 2001<p>
        how do you create a lightning the easy way??

        <p><p>
        
        <p>
        <hr><p>
        -- Posted by WebWyvern on 12:09 am on Oct. 20, 2001<p>
        Create a new layer. <br>Pick the Linear Gradient Tool. <br>With Black to White, drag from the top to the bottom. &nbsp; <br>Filter->Render->Difference Clouds. <br>Image->Adjust->Invert. &nbsp; <br>Image->Adjust->Levels. <br>Drag the middle slider to the right.  <br> <br>Thats just one way that is real easy..

        <p><p>
        
        <p>
        <hr><p>
        -- Posted by Kojaru on 1:04 am on Oct. 20, 2001<p>
        ei it works!! btw, it creates a random lightning ryt?? depending on the gradient direction ryt??

        <p><p>
        
        <p>
        <hr><p>
        -- Posted by xenocide on 1:06 am on Oct. 20, 2001<p>
        on a square image, you make a vert white bar, blur it as much as you want, then run the wind filter on it... &nbsp;After you have it pretty cool that way run polar coordinates filter on it .. rect²polar...  <br> <br>

        <p><p>
        
        <p>
        <hr><p>
        -- Posted by WebWyvern on 1:07 am on Oct. 20, 2001<p>
        yeah.. that one is random due to the difference clouds filter. &nbsp;theres many other ways to do it.. that one is just simple in my opinion

