        -- Posted by FreeStyler on 2:15 pm on Oct. 28, 2001<p>
        When you use the gradient-clouds-invert way to get the lightning how exactly do you get the black in the background to go transparent

        <p><p>
        
        <p>
        <hr><p>
        -- Posted by xenocide on 4:15 am on Oct. 30, 2001<p>
        set the layer that it is on to screen blending mode on the layers palette. &nbsp;That will let all light colors (white) through, and dark will be transparent.

        <p><p>
        
        <p>
